"summary": "Learn what doctors consider a normal menstrual cycle, how long periods usually last, and when changes may require medical attention.",
"content": "# What Is A Normal Period?\n\nMany people wonder whether their period is normal. The truth is that menstrual cycles vary from person to person. What is normal for one person may not be normal for another.\n\n## Understanding Your Menstrual Cycle\n\nA menstrual cycle begins on the first day of bleeding and ends the day before the next period starts. The average cycle length is about 28 days, but cycles ranging from 21 to 35 days are generally considered normal for adults.\n\nTeenagers may experience more irregular cycles during the first few years after their periods begin because hormones are still stabilizing.\n\n## How Long Should A Period Last?\n\nMost periods last between 2 and 7 days.\n\nNormal bleeding may:\n\n• Start light and become heavier\n• Include small blood clots\n• Gradually become lighter before ending\n\nThe amount of blood lost varies, but most people lose between 30 and 80 milliliters during a period.\n\n## Common Symptoms During A Normal Period\n\nMany people experience:\n\n• Mild to moderate cramps\n• Breast tenderness\n• Bloating\n• Fatigue\n• Mood changes\n• Food cravings\n• Lower back discomfort\n\nThese symptoms are usually caused by hormonal changes and often improve after the first few days of bleeding.\n\n## Signs Your Period May Not Be Normal\n\nConsider speaking with a healthcare professional if:\n\n• Your period lasts longer than 7 days\n• You soak through a pad or tampon every hour for several hours\n• Severe pain prevents normal activities\n• Your periods suddenly become irregular\n• You miss multiple periods without pregnancy\n• Large blood clots occur regularly\n• Bleeding occurs between periods\n\n## Lifestyle Factors That Affect Periods\n\nYour menstrual cycle can be influenced by:\n\n• Stress\n• Lack of sleep\n• Significant weight changes\n• Excessive exercise\n• Certain medications\n• Hormonal conditions\n\nTemporary changes do not always indicate a medical problem.\n\n## Period Tracking Is Important\n\nTracking helps you understand your body and identify patterns. Record:\n\n• Start and end dates\n• Flow intensity\n• Symptoms\n• Mood changes\n• Energy levels\n\nApps like Luna Cycle make it easier to identify trends over time.\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: Every woman should have a 28-day cycle.\n\nFact: Healthy cycles can range from 21 to 35 days in adults.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nA normal period usually occurs every 21–35 days, lasts 2–7 days, and may include mild cramps, bloating, and mood changes. Tracking your cycle can help you understand what is normal for your body and identify changes that may require medical attention."
