"summary": "Learn about the most common early signs of pregnancy and when to take a pregnancy test.",
"content": "# Early Pregnancy Signs\n\nPregnancy symptoms can begin surprisingly early, sometimes before a missed period. However, symptoms vary greatly from person to person.\n\n## How Early Can Symptoms Start?\n\nAfter fertilization, the embryo travels to the uterus and implants into the uterine lining. Implantation typically occurs 6 to 12 days after ovulation.\n\nHormonal changes begin shortly afterward and may trigger early symptoms.\n\n## Common Early Pregnancy Signs\n\n### Missed Period\n\nA missed period is often the first noticeable sign of pregnancy, especially for people with regular cycles.\n\n### Breast Changes\n\nBreasts may feel:\n\n• Tender\n• Swollen\n• Heavier than usual\n• More sensitive to touch\n\nThe areolas may also appear darker.\n\n### Fatigue\n\nMany people report extreme tiredness during early pregnancy. Rising progesterone levels contribute to increased sleepiness and reduced energy.\n\n### Nausea Or Morning Sickness\n\nDespite its name, morning sickness can happen at any time of day.\n\nSymptoms may include:\n\n• Nausea\n• Food aversions\n• Increased sensitivity to smells\n• Occasional vomiting\n\n### Frequent Urination\n\nHormonal changes increase blood flow to the kidneys, leading to more frequent trips to the bathroom.\n\n### Mood Changes\n\nRapid hormonal shifts may affect emotions and mood.\n\nSome people experience:\n\n• Irritability\n• Emotional sensitivity\n• Anxiety\n• Mood swings\n\n## Less Common Early Symptoms\n\nSome people may also notice:\n\n• Mild cramping\n• Implantation spotting\n• Bloating\n• Headaches\n• Dizziness\n• Constipation\n• Increased body temperature\n\n## When To Take A Pregnancy Test\n\nHome pregnancy tests are most accurate after a missed period.\n\nTesting too early may produce a false negative result because pregnancy hormone levels may not yet be high enough to detect.\n\n## Symptoms Alone Cannot Confirm Pregnancy\n\nMany early pregnancy symptoms are similar to PMS symptoms.\n\nBecause of this, symptoms alone cannot reliably confirm pregnancy.\n\nA pregnancy test or medical evaluation is needed for confirmation.\n\n## When To Contact A Healthcare Professional\n\nSeek medical advice if you:\n\n• Have a positive pregnancy test\n• Experience severe pain\n• Have heavy bleeding\n• Feel faint or dizzy\n• Have concerns about your pregnancy\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: Morning sickness only occurs in the morning.\n\nFact: Nausea can occur at any time during the day or night.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nEarly pregnancy symptoms may include a missed period, breast tenderness, fatigue, nausea, mood changes, and frequent urination. Because symptoms vary widely and often resemble PMS, a pregnancy test is the best way to confirm pregnancy."
